    <para styleclass="Notes"></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes"><anchor id="-NOTES-ElectricalSystem"></anchor>-NOTES-</para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="%s" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Notes" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; color:#231f20;">
      <li styleclass="Notes">Prior to performing maintenance of the servo amplifiers, spindle amplifiers, and inverters, turn OFF the main power switch and confirm that the LED which indicates charging (red) for each amplifier and inverter is off.</li>
      <li styleclass="Notes">High voltage current flows through components inside the junction box.</li>
      <li styleclass="Notes">High voltage current continues to flow on the primary side of the main power switch even after the main power supply is turned OFF.</li>
      <li styleclass="Notes">Electrical current continues to flow to lamps and outlets in the machine controller even after the main power supply is turned OFF.</li>
    </list>
